The formula (LibreOffice‑compatible) is:
```
=IFERROR(VLOOKUP(M5,$G$6:$J$30,4,FALSE),"not found - please re-enter")
```
This looks up the slip number from M5 in the range G6:J30, returns the 4th column (BookNo), and handles errors with the required message.
Code:
```repl
import openpyxl
from pathlib import Path

# Paths
input_path = Path(input_spreadsheet)
output_dir = Path("/sandbox/output/output_spreadsheet/")
output_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
output_path = output_dir / input_path.name

# Load workbook (preserve formulas)
wb = openpyxl.load_workbook(input_path, data_only=False)
ws = wb[wb.sheetnames[0]]

# Write the lookup formula into B2
ws["B2"] = '=IFERROR(VLOOKUP(M5,$G$6:$J$30,4,FALSE),"not found - please re-enter")'

# Save to output location
wb.save(output_path)

# Recalculate (LibreOffice)
recalculate(str(output_path))

# Verify by reloading with data_only=True
wb_check = openpyxl.load_workbook(output_path, data_only=True)
ws_check = wb_check[wb_check.sheetnames[0]]
print("B2 after recalculation:", ws_check["B2"].value)
```
